data.name: SentryObjectTextBox.ToolTip
data.value: Refers to a near earth object that is being monitored by NASA's sentry system. The sentry impact monitoring system scans the orbits of these objects, calculates their future positions, and flags any object with a non-zero probability of impacting Earth within the next 100+ years.

data.name: MissDistanceLunarTextBox.ToolTip
data.value: The closest distance that a near earth object will come to its orbiting body. Represented in lunar, the average distance between the Earth and the Moon. This is approximately 384,400 kilometers or about 238,855 miles.

data.name: MissDistanceAstronomicalTextBox.ToolTip
data.value: The closest distance that a near earth object will come to its orbiting body. Represented in astronomical, the average distance between the Earth and the Sun. This is approximately 149.6 million kilometers or about 93 million miles.
